.c .py .sh 
script file first must begin with #! python interpreter path/bash interpreter path(/bin/bash)
key is   couce code  to  executable
edit .c source code    then compile to execute file   gcc souce_code_name.c -o execute_name
edit .sh source code  then to execute it run bash(bash interpreter) souce_code_name.sh     
another is set execute permission to source_code_name.sh       chmod a+x souce_code_name.sh
edit .py source code then to execute it run python(python interpreter) source_code_.py    interactive with python in python interpreter  
another is set execute permission to source code .py  
find python interpreter path in current python intrepreter/script(interactive):import sys  print(sys.executable)









